Pergament, 94 ff., ca. 19,5 × 14 cm; 10. årh.
Håndskriftet er skrevet i flere hænder. Det har tilhørt Skt. Jacobs kloster i Liege, cf. ejernotis på f. 1r ("liber sancti jacobi in leod ...")
Det har i nyere tid tilhørt Georg Kloss i Frankfurt am Main
Bibl.: Ellen Jørgensen, Catalogus codicum Latinorum medii ævi Bibliothecæ Regiæ Hafniensis, Hafniæ 1926, p. 335f. - Carl P.E. Springer, The Manuscripts of Sedulius. A Provisional Handlist, Philadelphia 1995, p. 136

Parchment, 94 ff., ca. 19,5 × 14 cm; 10th century
The manuscript has been written by a group of scribes. It once belonged to the monasterium sancti Jacobi in Liege, cf. ownership notise on f. 1r ("liber sancti jacobi in leod ...")
In the 19th century it belonged to Georg Kloss in Frankfurt am Main
Bibl.: Ellen Jørgensen, Catalogus codicum Latinorum medii ævi Bibliothecæ Regiæ Hafniensis, Hafniæ 1926, p. 335f. - Carl P.E. Springer, The Manuscripts of Sedulius. A Provisional Handlist, Philadelphia 1995, p. 136
